impersonate or kill. During the night, you should inspect players whose identities are uncertain (there is no need to check players who are highly suspected of being werewolves).\nWhen speaking during the day, your goal is to convince others that you are the real Seer. You must gather trust and\nshare your findings without exposing yourself too early. Even though revealing your identity might put you in danger,\na Seer trusted by both the Witch and the Guard can survive for at least three rounds if everyone acts accordingly.\nA good Seer will coordinate with the Witch and the Guard to divide responsibilities. For example, on the first night, the Guard protects the Seer, and the Witch doesn't use the antidote. On the second night, the Witch saves the Seer, and the Guard protects someone else.\n\n\nWitch Role Introduction:\nYou are the Witch. Each night, you will be told who has been attacked, and you must decide whether to use your antidote\nto save them or use your poison to eliminate another player. You only have one poison and one antidote, so use them wisely.\nDuring the daytime discussions, if the night ends without a death, you can reveal that you used your antidote to save someone, which may earn others' trust.\nTypically, you should use the antidote to save key players like the Seer, the Guard, or yourself, while the poison is best used to eliminate werewolves at night.\nHowever, be cautious: sometimes the werewolves will deliberately attack one of their own (self-knife strategy) to trick you into wasting the antidote, thereby boosting their credibility.\n\n\nGuard Role Introduction:\nYou are the Guard. Each night, you can choose one player to protect from being killed by the werewolves. You cannot protect\nthe same player two nights in a row. Your role is critical in keeping important players like the Seer or the Witch alive.\nYou are in a constant mental battle with the werewolves, trying to predict who they will target. It might not always be the Seer, as the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Wilford, your role in this game is wolf.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Patricia': 'Robert', 'Marian': 'Jeffrey', 'Wilford': 'Robert'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Patricia', 'Marian', 'Wilford']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 5\n - Final Target: Robert\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nJames's speech: Good morning, everyone. I hope you all had a peaceful night. I want to start by thanking the Guard for their protection last night. It's crucial that we all work together to keep each other safe. As for the night itself, I didn't notice any unusual behavior that would make me suspicious of any particular player. However, I do think it's important that we remain vigilant and keep an open mind as we gather more information. Let's take our time to discuss and consider all possibilities before we make any decisions about who to banish. I believe that by working together and sharing our observations, we can identify the werewolves and ensure the survival of the village.\nJeffrey's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by thanking the Guard for their protection last night. Robert was safe, and I can confirm that the night was peaceful. This is a good sign, but we must remain vigilant. The Guard's protection was crucial, and we should consider this when making our decisions about who to trust and who to investigate further. Let's work together and share our observations to identify the werewolves and ensure the survival of the village.\nLeo's speech: Good morning, everyone. I hope you all had a peaceful night. I would like to thank the Guard for their protection last night, which ensured that Robert was safe. As for the night itself, I can confirm that it was indeed peaceful. However, I have some information that I believe is crucial for our survival. I am the Seer, and last night I checked Patricia's identity. I can confirm that she is a werewolf. This is a significant discovery, and I believe that Patricia should be our top priority for elimination. Let's work together and remain vigilant as we gather more information and make informed decisions about who to banish next.\nMarian's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by thanking the Guard for their protection last night. Robert was safe, and I can confirm that the night was peaceful. I would like to express my support for Leo's claim as the Seer. His information is crucial for our survival, and I believe that Patricia should be our top priority for elimination. As the Guard, I protected Robert last night, and I will continue to do my best to keep our village safe. Let's work together and share our observations to identify the werewolves and ensure the survival of the village.\nPatricia's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by thanking the Guard for protecting Robert last night. It's crucial that we all work together to keep each other safe. I would like to address the claims made by Leo and Marian that I am a werewolf. I strongly deny these accusations, and I believe that we should not jump to conclusions without more evidence. Let's remain calm and gather more information before we make any decisions about who to banish. I believe that by working together and sharing our observations, we can identify the werewolves and ensure the survival of the village.\nRichard's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to st